I needed to devise a sensible JSON structure. It has to encompass the whole campaign, so I included keys like `campaign_name`, `target_audience`, `key_selling_points`, `ad_copy`, `social_media_posts`, and `video_script`. This way, I can cover multiple advertising platforms within one unified JSON. I started brainstorming product names, finally settling on "CloudBum SoftFit Diapers". This name conveys softness.

The target audience is new parents, parents of toddlers, all seeking premium comfort and sleep for their baby. The key selling points are ultra-soft material, breathability, a stretchy waistband, and leak protection.

I then crafted the ad copy: headlines that resonate ("The softest hug your baby will ever wear.") body text emphasizing comfort, and a clear call to action. I came up with search ad copy and social media posts, describing the image or video concepts.

