    },
    {
      "year": "2013",
      "event": "LeFrak Center at Lakeside opens, completing a major 21st-century restoration of the park's lakefront."
    }
  ],
  "notes": [
    "Assumption: The history encompasses pre-colonial, design, modern alteration, and restoration phases.",
    "Architectural trivia: Olmsted and Vaux famously preferred Prospect Park's design over Central Park because the land acquisition allowed them to bypass the rigid constraints of a rectangular street grid."
